Here are all the files to do a viscoelastic flow problem in a four to one
contraction.

The fastq input file to build the mesh is:
four_one.fas

The exodus file containing the mesh: 
four_one.exoII

When doing viscoelastic flow calculations, generally you start with a Newtonian
solution and then use zeroeth order continuation in the time constant
to increase the amount of elasticity of the fluid. The Newtonian solutions 
files are:
newt.exoII
with the goma input for the Newtonian solution:
newt.input
newt.mat

A viscoelastic problem, with a time constant of 0.02 has been run from the 
Newtonian initial guess. The results are in:
ve.exoII
and the goma input files are:
ve.input
ve.mat
